def monthly_gcv_bar_plot(df1):
    months = ["April", "April24", "September", "October", "November", "December", "March24", "May", "June", "July", "Jan24"]
    normalized_gcv = (df1['Coal_QualityGCV'] - 3000) * 30 / (3500 - 3000)
    normalized_median=(((np.median(df1['Coal_QualityGCV'])- 3000) * 30) / (3500 - 3000))
    
    for i in range(1, 340, 31):
        j = i - 30
        monthly = df1[j:i]
        
        # Create a new figure for each month
        plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))

        # Bar plot for normalized GCV
        plt.bar(monthly.index, normalized_gcv[j:i], color='purple', label='Normalized GCV')
        plt.axhline(y=normalized_median, color='gray', linestyle=':', label='Median')
        plt.title(f'{months[i//31]} - Normalized GCV')
        plt.legend()

        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

monthly_gcv_bar_plot(df1)
